message.content: We know that in one hour, Mary can mow $\frac{1}{4}$ of the lawn, and Tom can mow $\frac{1}{5}$ of the lawn. So in 2 hours of work, Tom can mow a total of $\frac{1}{5} \cdot 2 = \frac{2}{5}$ of the lawn. Thus, the fraction of the lawn that remains to be mowed is $1 - \frac{2}{5} = \boxed{\frac{3}{5}}$ of the lawn.
